    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (NAVPAK) (1997) - SECTION 1.7: VEHICLE FEATURES - THROTTLE CONTROL FOR PTO
        OPERATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>THROTTLE CONTROL FOR PTO OPERATION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1900704">1.31</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                for the engine speed control flow chart.
            </para>
            <para>The T 444E engine is compatible with both stationary and mobile PTO applications. Remote and in-cab
                throttle control locations are available. Also, the throttle control feature can be used as an
                electronic hand throttle to be used during warm up procedures or cold weather idle operation.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1900704" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg1280" filename="../figeg1/eg1280.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.31 Engine Speed Control</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
    </svcsubsec>
